    "description": [
        {
            "text": "The  $\\textit{Ampere Turn per Metre}$ is the SI unit of magnetic field strength. \n  One ampere per meter is equal to $\\pi/250$ oersteds (12.566 371 millioersteds) in CGS units. \n  The ampere per meter is also the SI unit of \"magnetization\" in the sense of magnetic dipole moment per unit volume;\n   in this context $1 A/m = 0.001 emu per cubic centimeter$.",
